Congressman Donald McEachin was praised as a dedicated advocate for his community, a committed colleague, and a loving family man. He tirelessly fought for justice both in Virginia's General Assembly and the United States Congress. The speaker of the article mentions that they were elected to Congress and joined the Congressional Black Caucus together, working together to address important issues for the American people. The speaker expresses their honor in partnering with Congressman McEachin on legislation concerning environmental justice and a cleaner future. The article concludes with the speaker conveying their sorrow for the loss, sending condolences and prayers to Congressman McEachin's wife, Colette, their three children, and all those grieving.